Overview

Advancing Basic Education in the Philippines: ABC+ Project is USAID- funded project. The activity will work with the Government of the Philippines to support improved literacy in mother-tongue, numeracy, and social and emotional learning (SEL) in grades K-3.

ABC+ Project is hiring Technical Specialist for Basic Education to support the Second Congressional Commission on Education (EDCOM II). The Second Congressional Commission on Education (EDCOM II) was passed into law in July 2022 with the mandate of conducting a “comprehensive national assessment and evaluation of the performance of the Philippine education sector for the purpose of recommending transformative, concrete and targeted reforms in the sector with the end in view of making the Philippines globally competitive in both education and labor markets” in the next three years, from 2023 to 2025. The same law provides for the creation of a Technical Secretariat which shall provide technical and administrative support to the Commission.

In line with these aims, ABC+ Project is in need of a Technical Specialist with the relevant knowledge and experience in basic education.

Responsibilities

Scope of Work and Deliverables
• Handle the design, the timely implementation, and the efficient delivery, of the assigned committee’s work plan and milestones;
• Develop and manage the assigned committee’s budget;
• Organize meetings and consultations for the assigned committee;
• Undertake researches and data analysis for review of the EDCOM Commissioners, the Advisory Council, the Standing Committees, and the Executive Director, as needed;
• Draft monthly, quarterly, and annual reports for submission to the Commission;
• Prepare briefers, official communications, reports, and other documents, as needed;
• Manage a database and maintain relationships with relevant stakeholders;
• Prepare documentation required for meetings, consultations, and other activities; and
• Perform other tasks as may be assigned by the Chief Technical or the Executive Director.

Working Relationships
• Will report directly to the Chief Technical Specialist of EDCOM and ABC+ Chief of Party;
• Will serve as the main liaison between members of the Standing Committee, coordinating closely with the Chair, Co-Chairs, members, and their staff;
• Will work closely his/her counterpart in the Philippine Institute for Development Studies (PIDS) in relation to the research plan, and in the design of consultations;
• Will work closely with the Legal Consultant to map out existing and proposed policies, and to formulate bills for legislation; and
• Will work closely with the Communications Team to implement the communications and advocacy strategy, including but not limited to, the dissemination of research findings, the documentation of events/consultations, and campaigns relating to policy recommendations.

Qualifications
• Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field and 5 years of experience or Master’s degree and 3 years of experience;
• At least 4 years of relevant work experience in one of the six committees identified;
• Knowledge and understanding of the Philippine education system is preferred;
• Demonstrated capacity in project management;
• Able to gather, process, and analyze data with minimal supervision

1. Passenger services maintenance
• Maintenance of all the technical elements of passenger services (excluding electrical);
• Maintenance of lifeboat and tender davits and hydraulics;
• Available to supervise and assist the plumber/fitter with passenger service problems, and will be on

call to assist even when outside of scheduled working hours;
• Available for emergency maintenance periods in any engine related tasks, as requested by Staff

Chief Engineer or Chief Engineer;
• Must be familiar with the operation of all required machinery and be aware of its limits.

2. Reporting and monitoring
• Responsible for all aspects of technical USPH for engine spaces and technical equipment of

passenger services;
• Maintenance and purchasing routines in AMOS-win according to specified responsibilities within

the planned maintenance system, as directed by Staff Chief Engineer;
• Monitor spare parts stored and required for various sections of the machinery plant, as directed by

Staff Chief Engineer.

3. Other
• Duties include association with passengers so must be polite, courteous and presentable when

working in passenger areas;
• 1st Hotel Engineer will not hesitate to call out the Chief Engineer, Staff Chief Engineer, First Engineer,

Refrigeration Engineer and Electrician for assistance if in doubt of anything;
• Reporting of all defects and deficiencies found so that they can be rectified in good time;
• Promote a good working relationship and communication with the Deck Officers, Hotel Manager

and Guest Relations Manager to assist in efficient operation of the vessel;
• Be familiar with the Company Instructions and procedures relevant to position;
• Be familiar with the ship’s “Emergency Plan”, the “Muster List”, the ship’s “Code of Conduct” and the

“SQM”;
• Assisting Staff Chief Engineer in following up on poolside operations tasks.
• This job description is an outline of the duties and does not cover all responsibilities. The 1st Hotel

Engineer may be called upon to perform other ad-hoc duties when required.

Company description

IKEA is the world’s largest home furnishing retailer with 460 stores across more than 60 countries. IKEA Philippines is part of Ikano Retail, one of 12 IKEA franchisees and the only one owned by the family of Ingvar Kamprad, who founded IKEA in 1943.

IKEA Philippines creates a better everyday life by offering a wide range of well-designed, functional home furnishing products at prices so low, that as many people as possible can afford them. Ikano Philippines Inc. owns and operates the country’s first and the largest IKEA in the world – IKEA Pasay City – which offers an omnichannel shopping experience. To learn more, visit IKEA.ph

Job description

About the job

Reporting to the Customer Relations Manager, this TEAM LEADER role is to ensure a positive and joyful shopping experience for all IKEA visitors and customers. This is done by ensuring Easy Buying department is fast and efficient for our customers, and cost-effective for the IKEA store, handles customer’s issue in reliable and friendly way and supported co-workers in their daily work.

Your assignment

You will lead and manage the Easy Buying function in the store to fulfil the following:
• You build and retain a long-lasting relationship with new and existing customers in a multichannel retail environment by valuing and fulfilling customer needs and expectations thereby stimulating more frequent visits;
• You understand customer motivation and expectations and play an active role in turning them into commercial opportunities;
• You ensure a positive shopping experience that creates trust in the IKEA Brand before, during and after their visit;
• You keep areas of responsibility in shape as new and always keep work areas efficiently equipped during trading hours;
• You empower co-workers through knowledge, confidence, trust, authority and motivation so they are always ready to support customers in the best way possible;
• You are always available to deal positively and quickly with issues raised by customers;
• You lead by example in terms of customer focus, co-operation with other departments, simplicity and giving and taking responsibility to optimise customers’ experience;
• You are expected to assist customers to arrange for transport and assembly services through a well-managed Service or Home Delivery Desk

Qualification

Your profile
• You are passionate about home furnishing, people's life at home and the IKEA range of products and services;
• You have good communication and interpersonal skills
• You have ability to find solutions for customer and operational issues;
• You have good attention to details by being persistent, structured and accurate;
• You are able to accept criticism and deal calmly and effectively within high-stress situations;
• You are passionate about customers and act to ensure a positive shopping experience;
• You enjoy working in a fast-paced and future-oriented retail environment

More Information

We offer many benefits at IKEA other than just having the opportunity to work for a global company! Along with a focus on your personal and career development goals and being a part of an inclusive culture driven by values, you will be entitled to great initiatives including Annual leave, Medical and Dental, Family & Community leave, Co-worker discount, subsidized meals in our Co-worker Restaurant, Bonus program, full training and inductions.

This role requires flexibility in work hours, depending on store operational requirements.

Work Location is at IKEA Pasay City, Metro Manila, Philippines.

